            html: `<p>Tom loves solving puzzles and squashing bugs (the programming kind).</p>\n<p>As an engineer and “professional troubleshooter,” he inspires colleagues and clients with his unique approach — 60% patience, 30% creativity, and 10% humor. He is a champion listener and communicates well with just about anybody — from clients and stakeholders to programmers and designers. His decade of Drupal experience and previous work with nonprofits help him build user-focused experiences for the government agencies he now serves. </p>\n<p>Tom is a bartender-turned-developer and a self-taught expert in his field who still appreciates a well crafted cocktail. He loves getting outside with his wife to explore Colorado’s stunning wilderness — and he actually enjoys shoveling snow.</p>\n<h3>Things Tom has been doing</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Helping <a href="https://civicactions.com/case-study/msf/">Doctors Without Borders</a> raise support to deliver global aid</li>\n<li>Keeping government workings <a href="https://www.foia.gov/">open and accountable</a></li>\n<li>Leading the rebuilding of the <a href="https://home.treasury.gov/">U.S. Treasury</a> website</li>\n<li>Building tools and processes for <a href="https://civicactions.com/case-study/globalnet">international collaboration</a> </li>\n</ul>\n<hr>`,
